<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.1 Polk, Frank L.:
                        Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-05T22:00:00+01:00">September 5, 1919—10
                            p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                    <p>4061. Strictly confidential for the Secretary of State from Polk. Your 3019,
                        September 3. Very many thanks. Quite understand the situation and will
                        follow your advice. I do not look for the slightest friction now. Polk.</p>
                    <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                </div>
